Tools Used
MongoDB
MongoDB was chosen as the model component because its data model is documents with flexible, JSON-like schemas that correspond naturally with Python dictionaries, and records for animals are stored in a flexible manner. This made it easy to query, filter, and directly feed data into pandas DataFrames, without having to write a complex join or schema. The PyMongo driver also integrates seamlessly with the CRUD Python module created in Project One, which permits for a clean separation of the data layer and the logic for the dashboard.
Dash Framework
The application has a view and controller structure provided by Dash. The layout (dcc and html components) is the view, and Dash callbacks are the controller, receiving events on the filter input and changing the data table, pie chart, and map as a result. This is based on the MVC design pattern: MongoDB is the model, Dash layout is the view, and the callback functions (with the CRUD module) are the controller.
